Program: Start the Week
Title: 07/12/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00p50f5
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 7 Dec 2009
Andrew Marr explores whether the Enlightenment or communism is more relevant today, with Tzvetan Todorov defending the role of 18th-century thought and Tariq Ali demanding a re-evaluation of communist ideals. Andrew Graham-Dixon champions Russian art, and, on the 60th anniversary of Simone de Beauvoir's The Second Sex, Janine di Giovanni celebrates its enduring appeal. Show less